HEADWORD: Patroon
<hw>Pa*troon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>patroon</ets> a patron, a protector. See <er>Patron</er>.]</ety>
<def>One of the proprietors of certain tracts of land with manorial
privileges and right of entail, under the old Dutch governments of New
York and New Jersey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Patroonship</ent>⟦br⟧
